# Claude Code — agent label map for the usage statusline.
# Format: pattern|label      (first match wins; lines starting with # ignored)
#
# "pattern" is a substring matched against the session's cwd.
# "label"   is the string prepended to the statusline when matched.
#
# Override the file location with env var CLAUDE_AGENTS_CONF,
# or bypass entirely with CLAUDE_AGENT_LABEL (takes precedence).
#
# If you leave this file empty, the statusline falls back to a generic
# "🤖 <Name>" label whenever your cwd looks like .../agents/<name>/
# and shows no label otherwise.

# --- Examples (edit / remove freely) ---
# ~/projects/acme|🏢 Acme
# /home/me/work|💼 Work
# /opt/bots/alice|🤖 Alice
